<br>
I'm curious: in a large group, isn't the warrior's main deal to make sure everything attacks him?  The monk and rogue are supposed to deal more damage anyways, but the warrior is supposed to make sure he's still taking the hits.<br>
<br>
In that case, wouldn't high AGI and STA, and using a shield, be better than a high STR and a second weapon?  That way, you take fewer hits, healers aren't casting on you as often, etc etc.<br>
<br>
Come to think of it, couldn't this count if you're the ONLY tank?  Just curious, as I'm thinking about creating a warrior... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uerykaeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ErykaEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/01 12:32:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shield or not?</span><hr size=1> Second weapon = a lot more taunt than weapon/shield combo. While you would have higher AC, it wouldn't be as easy to get the mob's attention on you, which is especially crucial in the high 40's up to 60 when stuff doesn't respond to Taunt very well (if at all).<br>
<br>
